== Spectral sequence ==
Spectral sequences are important tools in algebraic topology for computing (co-)homology groups.

The Leray-Serre spectral sequence connects the (co-)homology of the total space and the fiber with the (co-)homology of the base space of a fibration. For a fibration formula_1 with fiber formula_155 where the base space is a path connected CW-complex, and an additive homology theory formula_156 there exists a spectral sequence:

:formula_157

